WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.916
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.838 --> 00:15.841
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:16.973 --> 00:20.933
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:21.064 --> 00:24.546
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.676 --> 00:27.984
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:30.769
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:31.379 --> 00:34.034
♪ ITS GONNA BE ALRIGHT ♪

00:36.949 --> 00:38.821
♪ CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.436 --> 00:49.353
♪ I'LL BE READY, I'LL BE READY

00:49.484 --> 00:53.357
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR,
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.708
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.839 --> 01:01.844
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:20.993 --> 01:22.778
♪ CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.908 --> 01:26.912
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.567 --> 01:33.528
♪ I'LL BE READY, I'LL BE READY

01:33.658 --> 01:37.532
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR,
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.662 --> 01:40.926
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.057 --> 01:45.931
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:02.034 --> 02:03.993
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

02:16.223 --> 02:18.921
[SIREN WAILING]

02:31.281 --> 02:33.196
-CUT THE SIRENS! TURN
THEM OFF! TURN THEM OFF!

02:33.327 --> 02:34.458
AND BRING ME SOME BLANKETS!

02:34.589 --> 02:37.983
[SEA LION GRUNTING]

02:40.682 --> 02:42.074
-HEY, IT'S GILLY.
-YEAH.

02:42.205 --> 02:44.033
-I'M NOT GIVING THIS
GUY MOUTH-TO-MOUTH.

02:44.164 --> 02:46.209
-SHE'S BLEEDING. IT'S THE GILL
NETS CUTTING INTO HER NECK.

02:46.340 --> 02:48.603
-AREN'T THESE GUYS BITES
LIKE TOXIC OR SOMETHING?

02:48.733 --> 02:49.865
-JUST GET BEHIND HER.

02:49.995 --> 02:52.694
[SEA LION BARKING]

02:52.824 --> 02:55.000
-I'M NOT REAL THRILLED
WITH THAT END EITHER.

02:55.131 --> 02:56.915
-WE GOT TO GET BETWEEN
HER AND THE WATER.

02:57.525 --> 02:59.179
SHE MIGHT BE GOING INTO SHOCK.

02:59.309 --> 03:01.572
[SEA LION BARKING]

03:01.703 --> 03:03.487
IT'S OKAY, GILLY.
IT'S OKAY, SWEETIE.

03:03.618 --> 03:04.923
STAY STILL, WE'RE NOT
GOING TO HURT YOU.

03:05.054 --> 03:07.056
-HEY, GILLY. HOW YOU DOING?

03:07.187 --> 03:08.318
[SEA LION BARKING]

03:08.449 --> 03:09.711
-STAY STILL, HONEY.

03:09.841 --> 03:10.799
[SEA LION BARKING]

03:10.929 --> 03:12.888
YOU GUYS, BE CAREFUL.

03:13.018 --> 03:14.716
-WE'RE NOT GOING
TO HURT YOU, OKAY?

03:14.846 --> 03:17.197
GET BEHIND HER. GET BEHIND HER.

03:17.327 --> 03:18.720
-HARVEY: WHICH
SIDE IS BEHIND HER?

03:18.850 --> 03:20.722
-OKAY, NOW, ON THREE
WE'RE GONNA DO IT, OKAY?

03:20.852 --> 03:22.245
ON THREE. ONE...

03:22.376 --> 03:23.115
-BE CAREFUL.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.683
-TWO, THREE!

03:25.814 --> 03:27.337
[GRUNTING]

03:27.468 --> 03:29.774
-OH, JEEZ! GREAT, WHAT
DO WE DO WITH HER NOW?

03:29.905 --> 03:32.212
[SEA LION BARKING]

03:32.342 --> 03:35.258
-MITCH, YOU NEED
TO TAKE CARE OF THIS.
-YEAH, I KNOW. GOOD MORNING.

03:36.259 --> 03:37.608
-DAD, WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

03:37.739 --> 03:39.175
ALL KINDS OF STUFF BEEN
GOING ON THIS MORNING.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.569
-TRUCK BROKE DOWN AGAIN,
I HAD TO HAVE IT TOWED.

03:42.874 --> 03:44.180
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

03:44.311 --> 03:45.877
-STEVIE'S UNCLE
WORKS FOR THIS COMPANY

03:46.008 --> 03:48.967
THAT CAN GET ME ALL THIS
HOCKEY GEAR WHOLESALE.

03:49.098 --> 03:51.753
WITH THE SKATES AND EVERYTHING,
IT'S ONLY 482 BUCKS.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.234
-HOCKEY'S GONNA HAVE
TO WAIT FOR AWHILE.

03:54.364 --> 03:56.192
-BUT YOU PROMISED.

03:56.323 --> 03:57.498
-YEAH, I KNOW I PROMISED,

03:57.628 --> 03:59.064
BUT WE JUST DON'T
HAVE THE MONEY.

03:59.804 --> 04:02.024
-MAYBE YOU SHOULD'VE
TAKEN THAT PROMOTION.

04:08.639 --> 04:09.771
-HEY, HOBIE.

04:11.555 --> 04:12.730
MAYBE NEXT MONTH, HUH?

04:12.861 --> 04:14.341
-HOBIE: SURE, DAD.

04:14.471 --> 04:17.344
-HEY, UH, MITCH I
COULDN'T HELP OVERHEARING,

04:17.474 --> 04:19.781
AND I THINK I HAVE THE SOLUTION
TO YOUR FINANCIAL PROBLEMS.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.522
-WHATEVER IT IS,
THE ANSWER'S NO.

04:22.523 --> 04:24.002
-SPONSOR A BIKINI CONTEST.

04:24.133 --> 04:25.874
-NO.

04:26.004 --> 04:27.528
-OH, COME ON, IT'S A MAJOR
RETURN ON A MINOR INVESTMENT.

04:27.658 --> 04:28.790
-NO!

04:28.920 --> 04:29.878
I DON'T EVEN HAVE ENOUGH MONEY

04:30.008 --> 04:32.054
TO INVEST IN REPAIRING MY TRUCK.

04:32.184 --> 04:34.056
-YEAH, BUT A BIKINI
CONTEST WOULD--

04:34.186 --> 04:35.710
-FREEZE, MILLER.

04:38.582 --> 04:40.758
NO CONTEST, THE ONE ON THE LEFT.

04:42.020 --> 04:43.892
-EXCELLENT CHOICE, CAPTAIN.

04:44.022 --> 04:46.503
TOUGH CALL. EXCELLENT CHOICE.

04:47.112 --> 04:48.723
-LAST MONTH, IT'S THE PLUMBING.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.899
THIS MONTH IT'S MY TRUCK.

04:51.465 --> 04:52.944
-YOU SHOULD'VE TAKEN
THAT PROMOTION, MITCH.

04:53.075 --> 04:55.556
-WHAT IS IT WITH EVERYBODY
AND THIS PROMOTION?

04:56.121 --> 04:57.819
ALL I NEED'S A
LITTLE EXTRA CASH.

04:57.949 --> 04:59.473
-HOW ABOUT A COUPLE
HUNDRED BUCKS?

05:00.038 --> 05:01.605
-I DIDN'T MEAN THAT. I
CAN'T BORROW FROM YOU.

05:01.736 --> 05:03.520
-GOOD, BECAUSE I
CAN'T LEND IT TO YOU.

05:03.651 --> 05:06.044
BUT THERE'S A PRIVATE PARTY AT
THE MALIBU COLONY THIS WEEK.

05:06.871 --> 05:09.657
THEY WANT TO HIRE A COUPLE
OFF-DUTY LIFEGUARDS.

05:09.787 --> 05:11.311
I'VE ALREADY
MENTIONED IT TO EDDIE.

05:11.441 --> 05:12.616
-I'LL TAKE IT.

05:12.747 --> 05:14.314
-DON: YOU GOT IT.

05:15.053 --> 05:16.620
-WE FIRST SPOTTED
HER OFF THE BELL BUOY

05:16.751 --> 05:18.230
WHEN SHE WAS JUST A PUP.

05:18.361 --> 05:20.058
SHE HAD THIS, THIS
GILL NET STUCK

05:20.189 --> 05:22.104
AROUND HER NECK SO WE
STARTED CALLING HER GILLY.

05:22.670 --> 05:24.672
BUT WE COULD NEVER GET CLOSE
ENOUGH TO GET IT OFF OF HER.

05:24.802 --> 05:27.239
AND THE MORE SHE GREW, THE MORE
IT JUST SLICED INTO HER NECK.

05:27.979 --> 05:29.285
-SHE KNEW WHEN IT
WAS TIME TO GET HELP.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.113
-YEAH, BUT SHE
SHOULDN'T HAVE HAD TO.

05:31.243 --> 05:33.202
WHY DO THEY KEEP USING THESE
THINGS? I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

05:33.333 --> 05:34.725
-BECAUSE FISHERMAN
DON'T SEE THE RESULTS

05:34.856 --> 05:36.510
OF WHAT THEY DO TO SEA
LIONS AND DOLPHINS.

05:36.640 --> 05:38.338
-WELL, I THINK WE SHOULD
GET THE PRESS DOWN HERE.

05:40.775 --> 05:42.472
-UNFORTUNATELY, AFTER
SATURDAY, THERE WON'T BE

05:42.603 --> 05:43.473
A DOWN HERE HERE.

05:44.779 --> 05:45.954
-WHY NOT?

05:46.084 --> 05:47.347
-MONEY.

05:49.740 --> 05:52.090
[SEA LION BARKING]

05:54.136 --> 05:55.659
-HOW MUCH DO YOU NEED?

05:55.790 --> 05:59.533
-I NEED $50,000 BY
6:00 PM SATURDAY OR ELSE

06:00.098 --> 06:01.535
WE GET TORN DOWN WITH
THE REST OF THIS PLACE

06:01.665 --> 06:04.364
WHEN THEY START BUILDING
OCEAN VIEW CONDOS.

06:05.452 --> 06:06.844
-HAVE YOU THOUGHT
ABOUT MAYBE ORGANIZING

06:06.975 --> 06:08.411
SOME FUNDRAISERS OR SOMETHING?

06:09.369 --> 06:10.674
-WITH ALL THE
NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS

06:10.805 --> 06:12.589
THAT NEED MONEY,
COME ON, SHAUNI.

06:12.720 --> 06:15.200
FACE IT, SAVING SEA MAMMALS
IS NOT PEOPLE'S TOP PRIORITY.

06:15.331 --> 06:16.593
-WELL, WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO WITH THE

06:16.724 --> 06:18.378
INJURED ANIMALS IF
ORCAS CLOSES DOWN?

06:18.508 --> 06:20.684
-SEA LIFE PARK IN SAN DIEGO
IS THE CLOSEST FACILITY.

06:20.815 --> 06:22.599
-THAT'S OVER A
HUNDRED MILES AWAY.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.775
THOSE ANIMALS AREN'T GOING TO
MAKE IT TRAVELING THAT FAR.

06:25.863 --> 06:28.431
-LOOK AT LEAST WE'RE HERE
UNTIL SATURDAY, AND HOPEFULLY,

06:28.562 --> 06:30.520
THAT WILL BE ENOUGH TIME
FOR GILLY TO MAKE IT.

06:35.177 --> 06:37.614
-AHH! HEY!

06:37.745 --> 06:39.399
-WELL, I REALLY
DON'T SPEAK ITALIAN,

06:39.529 --> 06:43.011
BUT IN FILM, WORDS DON'T
REALLY MATTER, DO THEY?

06:43.664 --> 06:45.492
-ISN'T SHE WONDERFUL?

06:46.884 --> 06:50.497
-DITA, BABY! TERRIFIC PARTY!

06:50.627 --> 06:53.021
-MARTY, YOU'RE LOOKING
UH, GOOD, THAT'S IT.

06:53.151 --> 06:54.022
-MAN: LITTLE FURTHER.

06:54.152 --> 06:56.067
-DON'T FALL! DON'T FALL.

06:56.198 --> 06:58.679
-MAN: OKAY. OKAY.

07:01.464 --> 07:03.031
-HEY!

07:03.161 --> 07:06.208
[SCREAMING] [PARTYING]

07:16.827 --> 07:18.960
-THIS PLACE IS ONE BIG
ACCIDENT WAITING TO HAPPEN.

07:19.090 --> 07:20.309
-TELL ME ABOUT IT.

07:20.831 --> 07:22.746
-EXCUSE ME, I DON'T THINK
IT'S A REAL GOOD IDEA

07:22.877 --> 07:23.834
TO GO SWIMMING RIGHT NOW.

07:23.965 --> 07:26.054
-I NEVER LISTEN TO IDEA MEN.

07:26.184 --> 07:27.621
-LOOK, I'D RATHER STOP YOU NOW

07:27.751 --> 07:28.926
THAN HAVE TO SAVE
YOU FROM DROWNING.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.754
-[LAUGHS] SON,
WITH ALL THE SHARKS

07:30.885 --> 07:32.452
AND BARRACUDAS AT THIS PARTY,

07:32.582 --> 07:33.757
IT'S MORE THAN LIKELY
I'LL HAVE MY ARMS AND LEGS

07:33.888 --> 07:35.629
CHEWED OFF BEFORE I DROWN.

07:35.759 --> 07:36.978
-WHOA! WHOA! I GOT YOU.

07:37.108 --> 07:38.022
-I THINK I'LL SIT DOWN.

07:38.153 --> 07:38.980
-OK.

07:39.110 --> 07:40.721
-HELLO, MY DARLING.

07:41.939 --> 07:43.854
[SIZZLES]

07:43.985 --> 07:45.595
-HEY! HEY! HEY!

07:45.726 --> 07:47.728
[SPLASH]

07:47.858 --> 07:49.904
WHAT IS WITH YOU? KEEP YOUR
FIRE UNDER CONTROL, WILL YOU?

07:50.034 --> 07:51.035
YOU ALL RIGHT?

07:51.166 --> 07:52.080
-YEAH, THANKS.

07:52.210 --> 07:53.734
-SURE.

07:54.909 --> 07:56.388
-WHO THE HELL ARE YOU TWO?

07:56.519 --> 07:58.565
-I'M MITCH BUCHANNON.
THIS IS EDDIE KRAMER.

07:58.695 --> 08:00.958
WE'RE THE L.A.
COUNTY LIFEGUARDS.

08:01.089 --> 08:03.308
-GOOD LORD, THE HIRED HELP.

08:03.439 --> 08:04.788
THE ONLY REASON
YOU'RE HERE IS BECAUSE

08:04.919 --> 08:07.182
MY INSURANCE
COMPANY REQUIRES IT.

08:07.312 --> 08:09.489
SO DON'T STOP ANYONE
FROM HAVING A GOOD TIME,

08:09.619 --> 08:11.229
JUST MAKE SURE NO ONE DROWNS.

08:11.360 --> 08:12.796
-YOUR FRIENDS KEEP
DRINKING AND SWIMMING,

08:12.927 --> 08:14.189
BELIEVE ME, SOMEBODY
IS GOING TO DROWN.

08:14.319 --> 08:15.799
-[LAUGHS] DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

08:15.930 --> 08:18.802
THESE AREN'T MY FRIENDS.
THIS IS BUSINESS.

08:18.933 --> 08:20.064
SO DON'T GET IN THE
WAY, OR YOU'LL BE OUT

08:20.195 --> 08:22.197
THE DOOR IN HALF AN HOUR.

08:22.893 --> 08:24.982
-BETTER CALL YOUR
INSURANCE AGENT.

08:26.288 --> 08:27.681
-WHY IS THAT?

08:27.811 --> 08:29.291
-WE'RE OUT THE DOOR NOW.

08:31.859 --> 08:34.078
-ALL RIGHT, HAVE IT YOUR WAY.

08:34.208 --> 08:35.558
DO WHATEVER IT IS
YOU PEOPLE DO.

08:35.688 --> 08:39.780
JUST DON'T OVERDO
IT. FAIR ENOUGH?

08:39.909 --> 08:41.956
-OKAY.

08:46.308 --> 08:48.832
-WHEN WE START FILMING
THIS IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS,

08:48.963 --> 08:51.574
UH, I PLAY THIS MARTIAL
ARTS INSTRUCTOR IN VENICE

08:51.705 --> 08:54.011
WHO'S ACTUALLY A
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

08:54.142 --> 08:56.361
AND HE KIND OF GETS
ROMANTICALLY INVOLVED

08:56.492 --> 08:58.712
WITH THIS BEAUTIFUL STREET
MUSICIAN. [LAUGHING]

08:58.842 --> 09:01.192
BUT YOU SEE, SHE'S ACTUALLY--
-WE DON'T WANT TO GIVE
THE PLOT AWAY,

09:01.323 --> 09:02.629
DO WE, DARLING?

09:02.759 --> 09:03.978
LET ME BORROW HIM
FOR A FEW MINUTES.

09:04.108 --> 09:05.849
I PROMISE I'LL BRING
HIM RIGHT BACK.

09:05.980 --> 09:07.242
EXCUSE US, DEAR.

09:08.373 --> 09:10.158
LARRY, DARLING,
CHARM THE PRESS.

09:10.288 --> 09:11.768
ALWAYS CHARM THE PRESS.

09:11.899 --> 09:14.379
BUT NEVER REVEAL TOO
MUCH ABOUT YOURSELF

09:14.510 --> 09:15.946
OR YOUR PROJECT, ALL RIGHT?

09:16.077 --> 09:18.514
-WELL, MY NEW FILM
COMES OUT IN TWO MONTHS.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.821
AND THIS TIME, I HAVE LINES.

09:20.951 --> 09:22.344
-THE COLLEGE OF SIENA--

09:22.474 --> 09:25.390
-VITTORIO, DARLING.
I'M SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

09:26.130 --> 09:28.089
-HOW ARE YOU?
-I SEE YOU'VE ALREADY
MET FERNANDO.

09:28.219 --> 09:30.178
-VITTORIO'S SEEN EVERY
ONE OF MY PICTURES.

09:30.787 --> 09:31.919
HE DOESN'T LIKE ONE OF THEM.

09:32.049 --> 09:33.834
[NERVOUS LAUGHTER]

09:33.964 --> 09:35.444
-VITTORIO, DARLING, I'D LIKE
FOR YOU TO MEET LARRY BROOKS,

09:35.575 --> 09:36.793
THE STAR OF OUR PICTURE.

09:36.924 --> 09:38.360
-IT'S A PLEASURE, SIR.
-PLEASURE.

09:38.490 --> 09:40.057
-LARRY, DEAR, THIS IS
FERNANDO, YOUR DIRECTOR.

09:40.188 --> 09:41.798
-I HOPE YOU LIKE MY PICTURES.

09:41.929 --> 09:44.061
-I ADMIRE EACH AND
EVERY ONE OF THEM, SIR.

09:44.192 --> 09:46.673
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I'VE
ALWAYS WANTED TO WORK IN ITALY.

09:46.803 --> 09:49.197
-DON'T MIND IF I DO. THANK YOU.

09:55.203 --> 09:57.205
THIS IS TERRIFIC. WHAT IS THIS?

09:57.684 --> 10:01.122
-I THINK IT'S
EITHER TOFU OR EEL.

10:01.252 --> 10:03.820
-[SPITS]
-HI.

10:13.351 --> 10:14.352
[SPITS]

10:18.443 --> 10:19.880
-WE'RE COMING BACK TO THE BOAT!

10:20.010 --> 10:21.446
-YEAH!

10:22.143 --> 10:24.145
-WHY DON'T YOU GET SOME REST?

10:25.886 --> 10:28.758
-HEY. WHY DON'T YOU
STAY IN THE POOL A WHILE?

10:29.541 --> 10:31.195
-I'M SORRY. I'M ON DUTY.

10:31.761 --> 10:33.110
-PITY.

10:35.417 --> 10:36.853
-UH, NO, SIR, PLEASE,
DON'T PUT THAT IN THE WATER.

10:36.984 --> 10:37.898
-MAN: WHY NOT?

10:38.028 --> 10:39.247
-BECAUSE I SAID SO.

10:43.425 --> 10:45.862
[SCREAMING] [PARTYING]

10:50.171 --> 10:51.781
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]
-YEAH!

10:52.869 --> 10:54.915
-GET THE BOAT BACK OUT.

10:55.045 --> 10:56.264
-PEOPLE: COME ON!

10:56.394 --> 10:58.614
[PARTYING] [SCREAMING]

11:02.052 --> 11:03.706
-GET THE BOAT BACK OUT!

11:03.837 --> 11:06.013
-HEY, IS THAT MY
AGENT ON THE PHONE?

11:07.231 --> 11:08.885
-PAST THE BREAKWATER!

11:09.016 --> 11:12.019
[PEOPLE PARTYING]

11:12.628 --> 11:15.239
GET IT BACK OUT! EDDIE!

11:17.459 --> 11:19.940
[WAVES CRASHING]

11:20.070 --> 11:22.507
GET THE BOAT BACK
TO BREAKWATER!

11:24.727 --> 11:26.250
-OHH!

11:26.990 --> 11:28.209
-EDDIE!

11:28.339 --> 11:29.297
EDDIE!

11:30.733 --> 11:34.606
[INTENSE MUSIC]

11:46.749 --> 11:48.664
-AH!

11:50.579 --> 11:53.103
[INTENSE MUSIC]

11:59.631 --> 12:00.589
-WHOA!

12:01.285 --> 12:02.243
-GET OUT THERE.

12:02.373 --> 12:03.461
-WHAT?

12:03.592 --> 12:05.159
-THERE'S A PRESS
HERE, BE A HERO.

12:05.289 --> 12:07.074
-DITA, I HATE THE WATER.

12:07.204 --> 12:08.684
-GO ON!

12:10.860 --> 12:13.602
[INTENSE MUSIC]

12:16.039 --> 12:17.911
-HERE! TAKE IT!

12:20.130 --> 12:21.218
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:26.571 --> 12:29.009
OKAY. IT'S GOING TO HELP.

12:40.324 --> 12:41.369
-I GOT YOU.

12:41.499 --> 12:42.370
HANG ON.

12:42.500 --> 12:44.589
[GASPING]

12:49.856 --> 12:52.032
-MITCH: EDDIE! OVER HERE!

12:52.162 --> 12:55.600
[INTENSE MUSIC]

13:09.658 --> 13:10.964
[GRUNTING]

13:16.317 --> 13:19.102
NO. LET GO! LET GO!

13:22.671 --> 13:24.629
NO! NO!

13:25.500 --> 13:27.023
LET GO OF THE LINE!

13:27.154 --> 13:28.938
DAMN IT! LET GO!

13:34.378 --> 13:35.858
[THUD]

13:44.388 --> 13:46.173
[COUGHING]

13:54.137 --> 13:55.573
-MAN: WHAT'S
GOING ON DOWN THERE?

13:55.704 --> 13:58.489
-ON THREE. ONE, TWO, THREE.

14:01.884 --> 14:03.364
ALL RIGHT, EASE IT IN.

14:04.452 --> 14:07.107
I GOT HIM.
-OK. ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

14:07.237 --> 14:08.412
-I'LL CHECK WITH YOU
IN EMERGENCY, HUH?
-LET'S MOVE IT.

14:08.543 --> 14:09.805
-EDDIE: ALL RIGHT.

14:10.458 --> 14:12.808
[SIREN WAILING]

14:16.333 --> 14:18.074
-HE SHOULDN'T HAVE
BEEN OUT THERE.

14:18.640 --> 14:20.033
-LUCKY FOR HIM, YOU WERE.

14:20.163 --> 14:22.513
-LUCKY FOR YOU, NO ONE
ELSE WAS SERIOUSLY HURT.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.126
-FOR SERVICES RENDERED.

14:27.475 --> 14:29.085
-I DON'T ACCEPT TIPS.

14:30.608 --> 14:33.263
-THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT
A HERO SHOULD SAY.

14:34.003 --> 14:36.353
YOU KNOW, YOU COULD
MAKE 10,000 TIMES THAT

14:36.484 --> 14:38.660
DOING WHAT YOU JUST DID
OUT THERE FOR THE CAMERAS.

14:39.704 --> 14:41.402
-WHAT, AS A STUNTMAN?

14:41.532 --> 14:43.273
-NO, AS A STAR.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.623
IF HE CAN DO IT, ANYONE CAN.

14:46.537 --> 14:48.278
I COULD HAVE THE
SCRIPT REWRITTEN,

14:48.409 --> 14:52.674
MAKE THE LEAD A LIFEGUARD,
WHO IS ALSO A PRIVATE EYE.

14:52.804 --> 14:55.155
BIG RESCUES, GREAT LOVE SCENES.

14:56.721 --> 14:57.722
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

14:58.506 --> 15:01.509
[MELLOW MUSIC]

15:08.908 --> 15:10.126
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS GUY TURNS DOWN

15:10.257 --> 15:12.215
AN OPPORTUNITY OF A LIFETIME.

15:12.346 --> 15:14.130
-I JUST DON'T WANT TO BE
IN SOME STUPID ACTION FLICK.

15:14.261 --> 15:16.176
-OH, COME ON, MITCH,
THEY MAKE MILLIONS!

15:16.306 --> 15:18.830
IT COULD'VE BEEN A WHOLE
NEW CAREER FOR YOU.

15:19.396 --> 15:20.832
-MY CAREER IS SAVING PEOPLE.

15:21.398 --> 15:22.791
-WHAT ABOUT SAVING ANIMALS?

15:23.357 --> 15:24.184
-WHAT'S WRONG?

15:24.314 --> 15:25.315
-GILLY.

15:25.446 --> 15:26.490
-HOW IS SHE?

15:26.621 --> 15:28.318
-EH, SHE'S BARELY HANGING ON.

15:28.449 --> 15:30.146
AND IF ORCAS CLOSES DOWN,
GILLY AND THOUSANDS LIKE HER

15:30.277 --> 15:31.582
ARE NOT GONNA SURVIVE.

15:31.713 --> 15:33.062
-EDDIE: WHY WOULD
ORCAS CLOSE DOWN?

15:33.193 --> 15:34.237
-WHY DOES ANYTHING
WORTHWHILE CLOSE DOWN?

15:34.368 --> 15:35.499
THERE'S NOT ENOUGH MONEY.

15:40.026 --> 15:43.159
-HEY, MITCH, DO THE
WORDS "DON'T FALL ASLEEP

15:43.290 --> 15:45.292
"IN THE POPPY FIELDS"
MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?

15:46.728 --> 15:48.382
-THE WICKED WITCH.

15:48.512 --> 15:51.559
-MM. THAT IS ONE HELL OF A
BROOMSTICK SHE RODE IN ON.

15:54.214 --> 15:55.476
-MITCH!

15:56.520 --> 15:57.478
LET'S TALK.

15:58.087 --> 15:59.436
-WHAT DO YOU GOT TO LOSE?

16:00.437 --> 16:01.743
FORGET I SAID THAT.

16:12.710 --> 16:13.885
-HARVEY: MITCH SHOULDN'T
BE ALONE WITH HER.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.670
SHE'S GONNA EAT HIM ALIVE.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.281
-I DON'T GET IT.

16:19.152 --> 16:21.589
I WAS THERE TOO, WAS I NOT? HUH?

16:22.155 --> 16:24.548
RESCUING PEOPLE, PULLING
THEM OUT LIKE TUNA.

16:25.506 --> 16:27.899
WHY HIM? WHY DID THIS DITA PICK,

16:28.030 --> 16:29.249
PICK HIM TO BE THE MOVIE STAR?

16:29.379 --> 16:31.512
WHAT DOES MITCH
HAVE THAT I DON'T?

16:32.121 --> 16:34.210
-EDDIE, MITCH ISN'T
GONNA DO THIS ANYWAY.

16:34.341 --> 16:36.996
-OH, MONEY, HONEY,
IT'S A GREAT MOTIVATOR.

16:38.998 --> 16:41.000
I CAN'T LET HIM BLOW THIS.

16:46.570 --> 16:47.832
-I DON'T GET IT.

16:47.963 --> 16:49.747
-YOU'D BE A
BELIEVABLE HERO, MITCH.

16:49.878 --> 16:51.532
THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE.

16:52.185 --> 16:54.230
WOMEN WILL FANTASIZE ABOUT YOU.

16:54.361 --> 16:57.233
TRUST ME, I KNOW
WHAT WOMEN LIKE.

16:57.364 --> 16:59.453
-THE ONLY TIME I'VE EVER
BEEN IN FRONT OF A CAMERA

16:59.583 --> 17:01.020
IS WHEN THEY
VIDEOTAPED MY WEDDING.

17:01.150 --> 17:02.064
-YOU'RE MARRIED?

17:02.195 --> 17:03.761
-DIVORCED.

17:03.892 --> 17:05.502
SO YOU CAN SEE HOW WELL
THAT PERFORMANCE TURNED OUT.

17:05.633 --> 17:07.242
[LAUGHING]

17:07.374 --> 17:10.420
-BEATTY, SELLECK-- THEY
HAVE THAT CERTAIN SOMETHING

17:10.550 --> 17:11.987
THAT MADE THEM A STAR.

17:12.117 --> 17:13.292
YOU HAVE IT TOO, MITCH.

17:13.423 --> 17:15.338
-NO, I DON'T. I,
I DON'T HAVE THAT.

17:15.469 --> 17:16.905
-LISTEN TO ME, MITCH.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.386
I ONLY PRETEND TO BE A BITCH

17:19.516 --> 17:22.780
BECAUSE IT SERVES ME WELL
IN A VERY TOUGH BUSINESS.

17:23.346 --> 17:25.305
AND I'M IN BUSINESS
TO MAKE MONEY.

17:25.435 --> 17:27.307
SO I WOULDN'T INVEST IT IN YOU

17:27.436 --> 17:29.483
IF I WASN'T SURE
YOU COULD DO THIS.

17:29.613 --> 17:30.701
-I'M A LIFEGUARD.

17:30.832 --> 17:32.660
-AND BOZ WAS A FOOTBALL PLAYER.

17:32.790 --> 17:34.096
ARNOLD WAS A BODYBUILDER.

17:34.227 --> 17:35.097
-THEY'RE PRO ATHLETES.

17:35.228 --> 17:36.620
-WHAT'S A LIFEGUARD?

17:36.751 --> 17:38.318
YOU'RE A PROFESSIONAL SWIMMER,

17:38.448 --> 17:40.581
AND SWIMMERS ARE
FANTASTIC ATHLETES.

17:40.711 --> 17:42.670
-MITCHIE, SWEETHEART!
SORRY I'M LATE.

17:42.800 --> 17:44.715
I SENT YOU A FAX FROM
THE CAR, DID YOU GET IT?

17:44.846 --> 17:47.631
HI. HARVEY MILLER, MR.
BUCHANNON'S PERSONAL MANAGER.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.242
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO
OPENING NEGOTIATIONS WITH YOU

17:49.372 --> 17:50.982
ON MY CLIENT'S BEHALF.

17:51.113 --> 17:53.681
-AH. YOUR, UH,
CLIENT DOESN'T SEEM

17:53.811 --> 17:55.117
WILLING TO ENTERTAIN MY OFFER.

17:55.248 --> 17:56.597
-OH. WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE I DO

17:56.727 --> 17:59.208
ALL OF HIS ENTERTAINING
FOR HIM. [LAUGHS]

17:59.339 --> 18:01.602
SO, WHAT KIND OF FIGURES
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT HERE?

18:01.732 --> 18:03.995
-WELL, I DON'T THINK
WE SHOULD DISCUSS MONEY

18:04.126 --> 18:06.433
IN FRONT OF YOUR CLIENT.

18:06.563 --> 18:08.522
-WE HAVE NO SECRETS FROM
EACH OTHER, DO WE, MITCH?

18:08.652 --> 18:09.653
-UH, NO.

18:09.784 --> 18:10.959
-I WANT TO SCREEN TEST HIM.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.439
-AFTER WE
PRE-NEGOTIATE THE DEAL.

18:12.569 --> 18:13.918
YOU KNOW, THE UP
FRONT, THE BACK END.

18:14.789 --> 18:16.138
-OF COURSE.

18:16.269 --> 18:17.835
-UPON SIGNING, HE
BECOMES PAY OR PLAY.

18:17.966 --> 18:19.228
-WITH A BUYOUT.

18:19.359 --> 18:20.751
-I'M GONNA NEED
NAME ABOVE THE TITLE.

18:20.882 --> 18:22.057
-ON THE SEQUEL, NOT
THE FIRST TIME OUT.

18:22.188 --> 18:23.537
-LET'S TALK MOTOR HOME.

18:23.667 --> 18:24.451
-DITA: A HONEY WAGON.

18:24.581 --> 18:25.321
-HARVEY: STAR WAGON.

18:25.452 --> 18:26.496
-DITA: FINE.

18:26.627 --> 18:27.280
-HOW MUCH UP FRONT?

18:27.410 --> 18:27.845
-DITA: 10,000.

18:27.976 --> 18:28.803
-40.

18:28.933 --> 18:29.934
-20,000.
-30.

18:30.065 --> 18:33.242
-25,000 ON SIGNING AGAINST 150

18:33.373 --> 18:34.591
ON THE FIRST DAY OF PHOTOGRAPHY.

18:34.722 --> 18:35.636
-IT'S A DONE DEAL.

18:35.766 --> 18:36.898
-DONE DEAL.

18:37.028 --> 18:38.334
WE'LL TALK.

18:41.816 --> 18:43.600
-25,000.

18:44.601 --> 18:46.429
-YES!

18:52.261 --> 18:55.438
[MELLOW MUSIC]

18:57.788 --> 18:59.703
-I KNOW I SHOULDN'T
BE DOING THIS.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.618
[GLASS CLINKING]

19:09.409 --> 19:10.845
NO, LET ME.

19:14.501 --> 19:17.156
I WANTED TO DO THIS THE
FIRST TIME I SAW YOU.

19:18.069 --> 19:20.202
-HOW COME IT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

19:20.333 --> 19:21.943
-MAYBE I WANT YOU TO SUFFER.

19:22.944 --> 19:25.294
OR MAYBE IT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE SO COLD.

19:30.691 --> 19:32.736
-THE ONLY THING COLD
ABOUT ME IS MY GUN.

19:32.867 --> 19:34.260
-THE ONLY...

19:34.390 --> 19:36.958
I CAN'T SAY THAT. WHO
WRITES THIS STUFF?

19:37.088 --> 19:38.612
-COME ON, MITCH, REMEMBER
WHAT WE TALKED ABOUT?

19:38.742 --> 19:40.396
WHAT IS YOUR INTENTION
IN THE SCENE?

19:40.527 --> 19:41.963
-TO GET THIS THING OVER
AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.

19:42.093 --> 19:44.139
-LISTEN, YOU WANT ME TO
SHOW HIM HOW TO DO IT?

19:44.270 --> 19:47.534
-EDDIE, THERE CAN ONLY BE
ONE DIRECTOR ON THE SET.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.057
-THIS IS A LIVING ROOM.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.667
-WHICH IS WHY YOU
ARE NOT THE DIRECTOR.

19:50.798 --> 19:52.234
NOW MITCH, LOOK, IT'S EASY.

19:52.365 --> 19:54.280
-I NEED THOSE HEADSHOTS BY SIX.

19:54.410 --> 19:56.760
AND MAKE SURE YOU TOUCH UP
THAT MARK ON HIS CHIN THERE.

19:56.891 --> 19:58.806
AND PUT THE GLINT IN
HIS EYE, YOU KNOW?

19:58.936 --> 20:00.286
A COUPLE OF THOSE
LITTLE WHITE DOTS.

20:00.416 --> 20:01.678
-HEY.
-HMM?

20:01.809 --> 20:02.897
-YOU'RE NOT UPSET, ARE YOU?

20:03.027 --> 20:04.246
-NO, NO, OF COURSE NOT.

20:04.377 --> 20:05.595
-I MEAN, BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,

20:05.726 --> 20:06.944
THIS IS JUST FOR
MITCH AND TO HELP...

20:07.075 --> 20:08.859
-YEAH, YEAH, I
KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW.

20:08.990 --> 20:10.121
-WELL, THEN WHAT'S WRONG?

20:10.252 --> 20:12.820
-NOTHING, NOTHING.
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:12.950 --> 20:16.084
-YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANT TO, WE
CAN PLAY THIS SCENE TONIGHT,

20:16.215 --> 20:18.739
AND I WON'T EVEN
MAKE YOU SUFFER.

20:18.869 --> 20:19.870
-OH YEAH?

20:20.001 --> 20:21.220
-YEAH.

20:22.308 --> 20:23.918
-MITCH, YOU CAN'T
CHANGE A LINE.

20:24.048 --> 20:25.528
REMEMBER, THIS IS A SCREEN TEST.

20:25.659 --> 20:27.095
YOU HAVE TO TREAT EVERY WORD

20:27.226 --> 20:29.271
OF THE TEXT AS IF
IT WAS SHAKESPEARE.

20:29.402 --> 20:31.578
I REMEMBER WHEN I WAS A
CONTRACT PLAYER AT FOX--

20:31.708 --> 20:33.232
-SHAKESPEARE WAS STILL ALIVE.

20:33.362 --> 20:34.885
[LAUGHING]

20:35.016 --> 20:37.801
-WHICH IS WHY CHILDREN
ARE NOT ALLOWED ON THE SET.

20:37.932 --> 20:40.630
ALL RIGHT, MITCH, TELL ME, WHAT
EXACTLY IS YOUR MOTIVATION?

20:40.761 --> 20:42.153
-YOU GOT ME.

20:42.284 --> 20:43.546
-MONEY, DAD. WE NEED
THE MONEY, RIGHT?

20:43.677 --> 20:44.504
-RIGHT.

20:44.634 --> 20:45.896
-RIGHT. READY?

20:46.027 --> 20:46.767
LET'S TAKE IT
AGAIN, FROM THE TOP.

20:46.897 --> 20:48.159
-HANG ON A MINUTE.

20:48.290 --> 20:49.204
COULD WE DO THAT
OTHER SCENE, YOU KNOW?

20:49.335 --> 20:50.292
LET ME JUST TRY THE OTHER SCENE.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.554
SHAUNI, NO OFFENSE OR ANYTHING.

20:52.076 --> 20:53.643
-EDDIE, YOU KNOW THE
LINES, YOU NEED THE SIDES?

20:53.774 --> 20:55.166
-THE WHAT?

20:55.297 --> 20:56.559
-THE SIDES, THE
WORDS, THE SCRIPT.

20:56.690 --> 20:59.432
-OH. NO, NO, I KNOW
IT, I KNOW THIS.

20:59.562 --> 21:00.389
-GOOD.

21:00.520 --> 21:01.695
WE'LL DO IT OVER HERE.

21:01.825 --> 21:03.131
-"HOLD IT RIGHT
THERE, YOU SCUZZ."

21:04.045 --> 21:05.699
-EDDIE, COME ON,
LET'S MAKE SOME ROOM.

21:06.352 --> 21:07.701
YOU KNOW, MOVE THAT BACK.

21:09.485 --> 21:11.139
AND USE THIS FOR THE CHAINSAW.

21:11.270 --> 21:12.271
-AH, RIGHT.

21:12.401 --> 21:13.968
-ALL RIGHT.

21:14.098 --> 21:16.057
EDDIE, YOU'RE A DRUG-CRAZED
KILLER WITH A CHAINSAW.

21:16.187 --> 21:17.232
HE'S GOT YOU CORNERED.

21:17.363 --> 21:18.712
HE'S UNARMED.

21:18.842 --> 21:20.148
BUT YOU KNOW HE'S DEADLY.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.410
READY?

21:22.019 --> 21:22.629
ACTION!

21:22.759 --> 21:23.934
[GRUNTING]

21:24.065 --> 21:25.980
[INTENSE MUSIC]

21:28.243 --> 21:29.766
[GRUNTS]

21:29.897 --> 21:33.030
MITCH. MITCH, LINE.

21:33.161 --> 21:34.423
-HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!

21:35.032 --> 21:36.077
SCUZZBUCKET!

21:36.207 --> 21:37.687
-SCUDBUCKET.
-SCUDBUCKET.

21:38.558 --> 21:40.124
LIKE SCUD MISSILE, DAD.

21:40.255 --> 21:41.561
-GOT IT, GOT IT.

21:42.170 --> 21:44.259
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE,
SCUDBUCKET.

21:44.390 --> 21:46.435
-STAY BACK, MAN,
OR I'LL CUT YOU!

21:46.566 --> 21:48.350
I SWEAR I'LL SLICE
YOU INTO TOOTHPICKS!

21:49.220 --> 21:51.222
-NO WAY. NO WAY.

21:51.353 --> 21:52.920
THAT THING'S ABOUT
TO RUN OUT OF GAS.

21:53.050 --> 21:54.225
-YEAH, WELL, I HOPE IT DOES

21:54.356 --> 21:55.662
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF YOUR SKULL!

21:55.792 --> 21:58.708
[LAUGHING]

21:59.796 --> 22:00.623
WHAT?

22:00.754 --> 22:04.105
[LAUGHING]

22:23.646 --> 22:25.213
[SEA LION BARKING]

22:38.357 --> 22:39.836
-WHAT'S UP, DOC?

22:39.967 --> 22:41.534
-HOW'S IT GOING, SHAUNI?

22:41.664 --> 22:44.101
-WELL, FROM THE LOOKS OF
THINGS AROUND HERE, NOT SO GOOD.

22:44.885 --> 22:46.669
-WELL, PACKING IS NEVER FUN.

22:47.714 --> 22:49.019
-HOW'S GILLY?

22:50.412 --> 22:51.370
-YOU WANT THE TRUTH?

22:53.197 --> 22:55.069
-NO, MAYBE YOU BETTER LIE.

22:56.244 --> 22:59.552
-WELL, I UH, I WOULDN'T
GET MY HOPES UP.

23:01.249 --> 23:04.295
-FRANK, WHAT WOULD YOU
THINK IF I DID SOMETHING

23:04.426 --> 23:08.256
FOR A GOOD CAUSE THAT I
WASN'T REAL CRAZY ABOUT DOING?

23:08.387 --> 23:09.605
-DON'T DO IT.

23:09.736 --> 23:10.867
-YOU DON'T EVEN
KNOW WHAT IT IS YET.

23:11.738 --> 23:14.871
-OKAY, BUT IF IT'S DANGEROUS
OR ILLEGAL, DON'T DO IT.

23:16.177 --> 23:18.353
-I'M TALKING ABOUT
A BIKINI CONTEST.

23:18.484 --> 23:22.792
[MELLOW MUSIC]

23:34.282 --> 23:36.632
-HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO TALK
WITH ALL THIS MAKEUP ON?

23:36.763 --> 23:39.026
-[LAUGHS] DON'T WORRY,
MITCH, WITH THIS SUN,

23:39.156 --> 23:40.462
IT'LL PROBABLY MELT
OFF AFTER EVERY TAKE.

23:40.593 --> 23:41.855
OVER HERE, OVER HERE.

23:41.985 --> 23:42.899
-OH, GREAT, I'LL
BE STANDING THERE

23:43.030 --> 23:44.161
WITH MY FACE IN MY SHOES.

23:44.292 --> 23:45.336
[LAUGHING]

23:45.467 --> 23:47.034
-YOU SHOULD SEE IT OUT THERE!

23:47.164 --> 23:49.210
-REFLECTORS, CAMERAS, ACTION.

23:49.340 --> 23:50.254
-I CAN'T DO THIS.

23:50.385 --> 23:51.952
-HOBIE: SURE, YOU CAN.

23:52.082 --> 23:53.606
-MITCH, YOU JUST DO IT
LIKE YOU DID IN REHEARSAL.

23:53.736 --> 23:54.955
-OKAY.

23:55.085 --> 23:56.043
-GOOD.
-WITHOUT THE GIGGLES, THOUGH.

23:56.173 --> 23:57.348
-YEAH, WITHOUT THE GIGGLES.

23:57.479 --> 23:58.262
-COME ON, YOUR OLD
MAN'S A NATURAL.

23:58.393 --> 23:59.307
THE CAMERA LOVES HIM!

23:59.438 --> 24:00.830
HEY, I SAW YOUR HEADSHOTS.

24:00.961 --> 24:03.093
THE GIRLS AT THE PHOTO
LAB WERE SWOONING.

24:03.224 --> 24:04.747
NOW COME ON, GET ON
OUT THERE AND SHOW

24:04.878 --> 24:07.228
THOSE AMATEURS WHAT A
REAL HERO IS MADE OUT OF.

24:07.358 --> 24:09.317
-COME ON, COME ON!
-ALL RIGHT, DAD, COME ON,
LET'S GO!

24:09.448 --> 24:10.840
-YOU CAN DO IT!

24:13.234 --> 24:14.278
-HOW DO I LOOK?

24:14.409 --> 24:15.236
-TERRIFIC. TERRIFIC.
-GREAT!

24:15.366 --> 24:15.845
-SUPER.
-AWESOME!

24:15.976 --> 24:16.846
-OKAY.

24:17.760 --> 24:19.283
ARE THERE A LOT OF
PEOPLE OUT THERE?

24:19.414 --> 24:21.372
-NO, NOT, THEY'RE JUST
ENJOYING THE SURF AND THE SAND.

24:21.503 --> 24:22.939
THEY'LL HARDLY
KNOW YOU'RE THERE.

24:23.070 --> 24:24.419
-HARDLY KNOW YOU'RE THERE.

24:24.550 --> 24:25.681
-JUST ANOTHER DAY
AT THE BEACH, RIGHT?

24:25.812 --> 24:26.943
-RIGHT!
-ANOTHER DAY AT THE BEACH.

24:27.074 --> 24:27.988
-YEAH.

24:30.077 --> 24:31.382
-RIGHT! RIGHT.
-RIGHT, THE BEACH.

24:31.513 --> 24:32.340
-RIGHT.

24:32.471 --> 24:33.689
-HOBIE: YEAH.

25:02.413 --> 25:05.939
-♪ THERE YOU GO, FEEL THE SUNSHINE

